Ghanaian Capital to Face Five, 12-Hour Blackouts by March 12

-- B y   J a s o n   M c L u r e
-- 
2011-02-11T10:43:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-11/ghanaian-capital-to-face-five-12-hour-blackouts-by-march-12.html
  Ghana ’s capital, Accra, will have
12-hour power outages on five separate days between now and
March 12,  Electricity Company Ghana Ltd . and  Ghana Grid Company
Ltd.  said in a statement.  Dates of the outages will rotate among neighborhoods during
the construction of a power line between the West African
nation’s largest city and a transmission station in the port
town of Tema, said the notice, published in the  Ghanaian Times 
newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jason McLure in Accra on 
 jmclure@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at  barden@bloomberg.net . 